## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the KmerTrash Next.js project.

### Implementation Summary

1. **Fetched Latest Documentation**: Retrieved the most up-to-date installation instructions from the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart)

2. **Installed Package**: Added `@vercel/analytics` version ^2.0.1 to the project dependencies using npm

3. **Integrated Analytics Component**: Added the Analytics component to the root layout following Next.js App Router best practices

### Files Modified

#### package.json
- Added `@vercel/analytics": "^2.0.1"` to dependencies

#### package-lock.json
- Updated with new dependency tree for @vercel/analytics and its 387 sub-packages

#### src/app/layout.tsx
- Imported `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag, after existing components (Header, main, Footer, JsonLd)

### Implementation Details

The Analytics component was placed according to the official documentation for Next.js App Router projects. It's positioned at the end of the body element to ensure it doesn't interfere with the page's critical rendering path while still tracking all page views and interactions.

The integration follows Next.js 14 best practices:
- Uses the Next.js-specific analytics package (`@vercel/analytics/next`)
- Placed in the root layout for site-wide tracking
- Preserves existing code structure and component hierarchy

### Verification

- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ ESLint passed with no new warnings or errors
- ✅ Type checking passed during build
- ✅ All existing functionality preserved
- ✅ Lock files properly updated

### Next Steps

To enable analytics in production:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the project's Analytics tab in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click "Enable" to activate Web Analytics
4. Analytics data will begin collecting after deployment

The Analytics component is now ready and will automatically start tracking page views and web vitals once enabled in the Vercel dashboard.
